---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="XRPL API Documentation - XRP Ledger Node Endpoint | XRPL Stream" description="Connect to XRPL Stream full history nodes. WebSocket, JSON-RPC, xrpl.js, and Python examples. Mainnet, testnet, and devnet. Free tier available." schema={{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "TechArticle",
  "headline": "XRPL Stream API Documentation",
  "description": "Complete guide to connecting to XRPL Stream full history XRP Ledger nodes via WebSocket, JSON-RPC, xrpl.js, and Python.",
  "url": "https://xrpl.stream/docs",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "XRPL Stream" }
}}>
  <Header />

  <div class="docs">
    <div class="docs-header">
      <h1>XRPL Stream API Documentation</h1>
      <a href="/openapi.json" download="openapi.json" class="openapi-btn">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M8 1v9m0 0L5 7m3 3l3-3M2 12v1a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2v-1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        OpenAPI Spec
      </a>
    </div>

    <section id="quickstart">
      <h2>Quick Start</h2>
      <p>XRPL Stream is a drop-in replacement for any XRPL endpoint. Replace your URL and you're connected.</p>

      <h3>Your Endpoint</h3>
      <p>After signing in, you get a unique endpoint URL:</p>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">HTTP</div>
        <pre>https://s1.xrpl.stream/e/xm_live_your_token_here</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">WebSocket</div>
        <pre>wss://s1.xrpl.stream/e/xm_live_your_token_here</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Sign in at <a href="/dashboard">xrpl.stream/dashboard</a> to get your endpoint.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="http">
      <h2>HTTP JSON-RPC</h2>
      <p>Send a POST request with your XRPL command as JSON.</p>

      <h3>Using your endpoint URL (recommended)</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">curl</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/e/YOUR_TOKEN \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"account_info","account":"rN7n3...","ledger_index":"validated"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Using X-API-Key header</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">curl</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/ \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-API-Key: xm_live_your_token_here" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"server_info"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Without authentication (free tier, lower limits)</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">curl</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/ \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"server_info"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="websocket">
      <h2>WebSocket</h2>
      <p>Connect via WebSocket for subscriptions and streaming.</p>

      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">JavaScript</div>
        <pre>const ws = new WebSocket('wss://s1.xrpl.stream/e/YOUR_TOKEN');

ws.onopen = () => {'{'}
  ws.send(JSON.stringify({'{'}
    command: 'subscribe',
    streams: ['ledger']
  {'}'}));
{'}'};

ws.onmessage = (msg) => {'{'}
  console.log(JSON.parse(msg.data));
{'}'};</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="xrpljs">
      <h2>xrpl.js</h2>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">JavaScript</div>
        <pre>import {'{'} Client {'}'} from 'xrpl';

const client = new Client('wss://s1.xrpl.stream/e/YOUR_TOKEN');
await client.connect();

const info = await client.request({'{'}
  command: 'account_info',
  account: 'rN7n3473SoZtKGBB5JnUB29hMcFSfZaV7v',
  ledger_index: 'validated'
{'}'});

console.log(info.result.account_data);</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="python">
      <h2>Python</h2>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">Python</div>
        <pre>import requests

resp = requests.post(
    'https://s1.xrpl.stream/e/YOUR_TOKEN',
    json={'{'}
        'method': 'account_info',
        'params': [{'{'}
            'account': 'rN7n3473SoZtKGBB5JnUB29hMcFSfZaV7v',
            'ledger_index': 'validated'
        {'}'}]
    {'}'}
)

print(resp.json()['result']['account_data'])</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="response-headers">
      <h2>Response Headers</h2>
      <p>Every response includes rate limit info:</p>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <tr><th>Header</th><th>Description</th></tr>
          <tr><td><code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code></td><td>Your plan's requests per second</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code></td><td>Tokens remaining in current window</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>Cache-Control</code></td><td><code>immutable</code> for validated data</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="errors">
      <h2>Error Responses</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <tr><th>Status</th><th>Error</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
          <tr><td>401</td><td><code>invalid_endpoint</code></td><td>Token not recognized</td></tr>
          <tr><td>403</td><td><code>endpoint_disabled</code></td><td>Account deactivated</td></tr>
          <tr><td>429</td><td><code>rate_limited</code></td><td>Exceeded requests per second</td></tr>
          <tr><td>429</td><td><code>monthly_quota_exceeded</code></td><td>Monthly credits exhausted</td></tr>
          <tr><td>400</td><td><code>invalid_json</code></td><td>Request body not valid JSON</td></tr>
          <tr><td>400</td><td><code>missing method or command</code></td><td>No command in payload</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="credits">
      <h2>Credits</h2>
      <p>Each API request consumes a small number of credits from your monthly allowance.</p>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Rate Limit</th><th>Monthly Credits</th><th>Price</th></tr>
          <tr><td>No key</td><td>5 req/s</td><td>1M</td><td>Free</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Free</td><td>15 req/s</td><td>10M</td><td>Free (key required)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Builder</td><td>50 req/s</td><td>100M</td><td>$29/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Pro</td><td>150 req/s</td><td>500M</td><td>$79/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Scale</td><td>300 req/s</td><td>2B</td><td>$199/mo</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features">
      <h2>What You Get</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Full history reads and transaction submission from one endpoint</li>
        <li>Mainnet, testnet, and devnet supported</li>
        <li>Global edge network for low-latency worldwide coverage</li>
        <li>WebSocket subscriptions (ledger, transactions, accounts, order books)</li>
        <li>Automatic failover, load balancing, and self-healing peer mesh</li>
        <li>Free tier with no credit card required</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="full-history">
      <h2>Full History & Transaction Submission</h2>
      <p>XRPL Stream provides access to the complete XRP Ledger history -every transaction and ledger close since <a href="https://xrpl.org/docs/concepts/networks-and-servers/ledger-history" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ledger #32570</a> (the earliest available). Unlike most public endpoints that only keep recent history, XRPL Stream serves validated data from genesis.</p>
      <p>The network includes both full history nodes and submission nodes. Historical queries, NFT lookups, and account data are served from optimized read infrastructure, while transaction submissions and live ledger commands are routed to nodes connected directly to the XRP Ledger peer network.</p>
      <p>Routing is automatic and transparent -you use the same endpoint for everything. No configuration needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="supported-commands">
      <h2>Supported Commands</h2>
      <p>XRPL Stream supports every public XRPL API command. For the complete reference, see the <a href="https://xrpl.org/docs/references/http-websocket-apis/public-api-methods" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official XRPL API documentation</a>.</p>

      <h3>Account Methods</h3>
      <p><code>account_info</code> <code>account_lines</code> <code>account_channels</code> <code>account_currencies</code> <code>account_nfts</code> <code>account_objects</code> <code>account_offers</code> <code>account_tx</code> <code>gateway_balances</code> <code>noripple_check</code></p>

      <h3>Ledger Methods</h3>
      <p><code>ledger</code> <code>ledger_closed</code> <code>ledger_current</code> <code>ledger_data</code> <code>ledger_entry</code></p>

      <h3>Transaction Methods</h3>
      <p><code>tx</code> <code>transaction_entry</code> <code>submit</code> <code>submit_multisigned</code></p>

      <h3>Order Book & Path</h3>
      <p><code>book_offers</code> <code>book_changes</code> <code>deposit_authorized</code> <code>ripple_path_find</code> <code>amm_info</code></p>

      <h3>NFT Methods (via Clio)</h3>
      <p><code>nft_info</code> <code>nft_buy_offers</code> <code>nft_sell_offers</code> <code>nft_history</code> <code>nfts_by_issuer</code></p>

      <h3>Server Methods</h3>
      <p><code>server_info</code> <code>server_state</code> <code>server_definitions</code> <code>fee</code> <code>manifest</code></p>

      <h3>Subscriptions (WebSocket)</h3>
      <p><code>subscribe</code> <code>unsubscribe</code> -streams: <code>ledger</code>, <code>transactions</code>, <code>transactions_proposed</code>, account activity, order books</p>
    </section>

    <section id="rate-limits">
      <h2>Rate Limits & Fair Use</h2>
      <p>All plans are subject to rate limits that ensure consistent performance across the network.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Throttling</strong> -Requests exceeding your plan's rate limit return HTTP <code>429</code> with <code>rate_limited</code>. Check <code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code> and <code>Retry-After</code> headers.</li>
        <li><strong>Burst allowance</strong> -Short bursts above the sustained limit are permitted. Prolonged high-throughput traffic should align with your plan tier.</li>
        <li><strong>Abuse prevention</strong> -Patterns consistent with scraping or denial-of-service result in temporary IP-level blocks.</li>
        <li><strong>No authentication required</strong> for the free public tier -just send requests. Create a free API key for higher limits.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="networks">
      <h2>Networks</h2>
      <p>XRPL Stream supports mainnet, testnet, and devnet. Add <code>/testnet</code> or <code>/devnet</code> to any endpoint path to switch networks. All features (caching, rate limiting, WebSocket subscriptions) work identically across networks.</p>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <tr><th>Network</th><th>HTTP Endpoint</th><th>WebSocket</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          <tr><td>Mainnet</td><td><code>https://s1.xrpl.stream/</code></td><td><code>wss://s1.xrpl.stream/</code></td><td>Live</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Testnet</td><td><code>https://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet</code></td><td><code>wss://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet</code></td><td>Live</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Devnet</td><td><code>https://s1.xrpl.stream/devnet</code></td><td><code>wss://s1.xrpl.stream/devnet</code></td><td>Live</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3>HTTP JSON-RPC</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">Testnet</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"server_info"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">Devnet</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/devnet \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"server_info"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>With Authentication</h3>
      <p>Works with endpoint tokens, API key headers, and query params:</p>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">Endpoint token</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/e/YOUR_TOKEN/testnet \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"account_info","account":"rPT1Sjq2YGrBMTttX4GZHjKu9dyfzbpAYe","ledger_index":"validated"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">X-API-Key header</div>
        <pre>curl -X POST https://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "X-API-Key: xm_live_your_token_here" \
  -d '{"{"}command":"server_info"{"}"}'</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>WebSocket</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">JavaScript</div>
        <pre>const ws = new WebSocket('wss://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet');

ws.onopen = () => {'{'}
  ws.send(JSON.stringify({'{'}
    command: 'subscribe',
    streams: ['ledger']
  {'}'}));
{'}'};

ws.onmessage = (msg) => {'{'}
  console.log(JSON.parse(msg.data));
{'}'};</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>xrpl.js</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">JavaScript</div>
        <pre>import {'{'} Client {'}'} from 'xrpl';

// Testnet
const client = new Client('wss://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet');
await client.connect();

// Devnet
const devClient = new Client('wss://s1.xrpl.stream/devnet');
await devClient.connect();</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Python</h3>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">Python</div>
        <pre>import requests

# Testnet
resp = requests.post(
    'https://s1.xrpl.stream/testnet',
    json={'{'}
        'method': 'server_info',
        'params': [{'{'}{'}'}]
    {'}'}
)
print(resp.json()['result']['info']['network_id'])  # 1</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>GET API</h3>
      <p>The REST-style GET API also supports network prefixes:</p>
      <div class="code">
        <div class="code-label">curl</div>
        <pre># Testnet transaction lookup
curl https://s1.xrpl.stream/v1/testnet/tx/YOUR_TX_HASH

# Devnet ledger
curl https://s1.xrpl.stream/v1/devnet/ledger/validated</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="resources">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://xrpl.org/docs/references/http-websocket-apis/public-api-methods" target="_blank" rel="noopener">XRPL API Reference</a> -complete command documentation</li>
        <li><a href="https://xrpl.org/docs/concepts/networks-and-servers/ledger-history" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ledger History</a> -how XRPL stores and serves historical data</li>
        <li><a href="https://xrpl.org/blog/2022/introducing-clio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Introducing Clio</a> -the optimized XRPL API server</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/XRPLF/clio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clio on GitHub</a> -source code and documentation</li>
        <li><a href="https://js.xrpl.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">xrpl.js</a> -JavaScript/TypeScript client library</li>
        <li><a href="https://xrpl-py.readthedocs.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">xrpl-py</a> -Python client library</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .docs-header { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .docs-header h1 { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .openapi-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 8px 16px; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.15s; white-space: nowrap; }
  .openapi-btn:hover { background: var(--surface); color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .docs { max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 40px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 48px; margin-bottom: 12px; padding-top: 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  h2:first-of-type { border-top: none; margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
  h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  p { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .note { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .code { border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .code-label { background: var(--surface); padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-dim); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  pre { background: #0a0a0a; padding: 16px; margin: 0; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; overflow-x: auto; font-family: var(--mono); }
  .table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  th { text-align: left; padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--surface); color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  td { padding: 8px 14px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-muted); }
  td code, th code { color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.78rem; }
  ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  ul li { padding: 6px 0 6px 18px; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem; }
  ul li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 14px; width: 5px; height: 5px; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 50%; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .docs { padding: 32px 16px; }
    h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    pre { font-size: 0.75rem; padding: 12px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .docs { padding: 24px 12px; }
    h1 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    pre { font-size: 0.68rem; padding: 10px; }
    .table-wrap { font-size: 0.75rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1rem; }
    h3 { font-size: 0.9rem; }
  }
</style>
